Interface FutureProcessor<T1,T2>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - the type expected from the Futures chain
    T2 - the type emitted as a Future from the processor
    All Superinterfaces:
    Function<io.vertx.core.Future<T1>,io.vertx.core.Future<T2>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CallProcessor<T,R>, IfProcessor<T,R>, MapProcessor<T,R>, PeekProcessor<T>, RunProcessor<T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface FutureProcessor<T1,T2>
extends Function<io.vertx.core.Future<T1>,io.vertx.core.Future<T2>>
